## Recommendation

The **top 4** (localization, local-storage, app-config, ci-cd) are the highest-impact additions because:

- **Localization** — you already mandate `context.l10n` everywhere but have no rules governing HOW to structure it
- **Local Storage** — isar is your DB but there's nothing on schema patterns, migrations, or offline sync
- **App Config** — every real app needs flavors/environments, and without rules agents will hardcode configs
- **CI/CD** — you mandate "tests must pass before PR" but don't define the pipeline

The **medium 3** (Firebase, forms, debugging) are valuable as the app grows more complex.

**Platform channels** can be folded into `architecture` as a section rather than a standalone skill.

> [!TIP]
> If you want to keep the skill count manageable, you could also merge `localization` into `clean-code` (since it's about code standards) and `app-config` into `architecture` (since it's about project structure). That would keep you at 12 skills instead of 14.
